JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma says the ANC's policy conference has been a success so far.Speaking on the side-lines of the five-day conference, Zuma says debate over the party's future has been frank and robust.READ - ANC NPC: What are the issues?But despite the president's claims, reports continue to emerge of ongoing factionalism among delegates as the party heads toward its December elective conference.Most of day four of the conference saw delegates behind closed discussing key policy issues, like transformation and discipline.Vuyo Mvoko sat down with political analysts, Karima Brown and Ebrahim Fakir to wrap up what was said ... and what wasn't.